# The working tree is shared between Windows git (autocrlf=true) and WSL
# git (no conversion) via /mnt/d — the same checkout must look clean to
# both, or WSL builds stamp a phantom -dirty into `git describe`. Force LF
# in the working tree for all text: Go, PowerShell, and every tool in this
# repo handle LF on Windows fine, and identical bytes on disk is the only
# state both gits agree on.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.exe binary
